---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About - SkanPay"
  description="Learn about SkanPay's patent-pending QR payment gateway work and the team building practical merchant checkout experiences."
  activePath="/about/"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About SkanPay</p>
    <h1>Building practical QR payment infrastructure for in-store commerce</h1>
    <p>SkanPay is focused on merchant checkout, payment app participation, and patent-pending QR payment gateway work.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div>
      <h2>Built around the checkout moment</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">The company keeps the product story grounded: clear payment flow, clear operating scope, and clear partner conversations.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="split-panel">
      <h3>What guides the work</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Make QR payment understandable for merchants and customers.</li>
        <li>Keep payment claims clear, accurate, and grounded.</li>
        <li>Support partner conversations with practical operational language.</li>
        <li>Advance patent-pending work around QR payment acceptance.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Team</p>
        <h2>Payment knowledge, product building, and business execution</h2>
      </div>
      <p>The team combines payment-domain expertise with hands-on product development and partner-facing business work.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="team-grid">
      <article class="team-card">
        <div class="avatar-placeholder" aria-hidden="true">KC</div>
        <span>Product and implementation</span>
        <h3>Kelly Chen</h3>
        <p>Kelly leads product direction, user experience, and hands-on implementation for the SkanPay website and BeamCash demo. Her work focuses on making QR checkout understandable for merchants, buyers, and partners.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="team-card">
        <div class="avatar-placeholder" aria-hidden="true">BC</div>
        <span>Payment expertise</span>
        <h3>Bilin Chen</h3>
        <p>Bilin brings deep payment-industry knowledge to SkanPay, with a focus on payment gateway models, merchant acceptance, and the practical requirements behind in-store transaction flows.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="team-card">
        <div class="avatar-placeholder" aria-hidden="true">ZL</div>
        <span>Business and market development</span>
        <h3>Zoe Lu</h3>
        <p>Zoe supports business development, market communication, and partner-facing positioning so SkanPay can explain the opportunity clearly to merchants, financial partners, and payment apps.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section patent-band">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Invention</p>
      <h2>Patent-pending QR payment gateway work</h2>
      <p>
        SkanPay has pending patent work related to its QR payment acceptance approach. The website keeps public claims focused while preserving room for deeper technical and legal detail in direct conversations.
      </p>
    </div>
    <a class="button primary" href="/contact/">Discuss SkanPay</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
